-- IFC Buys 15% Stake in Insurer Medgulf for $124 Million
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-02-08T15:55:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/ifc-buys-15-stake-in-insurer-medgulf-for-124-million-correct-.html
(Corrects location of company in headline and second
paragraph of story first published on Feb. 4)  The International Finance Corp. said
it agreed to buy a 15 percent stake in  Mediterranean & Gulf
Insurance & Reinsurance Co.  BSC for $124 million.  Medgulf , as the insurer is known, will use the funds to
expand into  Turkey , Iraq and Egypt, the investment arm of the
 World Bank  said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Cairo at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
